================================================================================
Significant external influences (ideas, SQL patterns, layout concepts)
================================================================================

The Monitoring deep-dive (Logs sub-views: Queries / Patterns / By table /
Histogram, plus Parts, Schema doctor, Cluster activity, and the Query
timeline chart) is heavily inspired by QueryDog by Benjamin Wootton
(https://github.com/benjaminwootton/QueryDog), which is licensed under the
Elastic License 2.0.

No QueryDog source code is included in this repository. The CHouse UI
Monitoring features were rebuilt from scratch on top of React 19 + shadcn/ui
+ recharts + the editorial design system. The following ideas, however, were
adapted from QueryDog and deserve explicit credit:

  - Dense "chart + sub-tabs + paginated table" Monitoring layout
  - Aggregation patterns over system.query_log (countIf by query_kind,
    normalizeQuery() rollup, arrayJoin(tables) per-table rollup)
  - Schema lint shape (Nullable & oversized integer audits against
    system.parts_columns)
  - The Query views log / Profile events drill-down concept

ClickHouse system table SQL (system.query_log, system.part_log,
system.mutations, system.replication_queue, system.asynchronous_metrics,
etc.) follows the conventions in the ClickHouse documentation and is not
proprietary to QueryDog.

For the full list of dependencies and their licenses, please refer to the
package.json files.
